[2
Date: 23 Aug 2001
From: Alejandro A Schudel <incoalex@mail.retina.ar> [edited

In our experience over the years, [South American camelids have low
susceptibility to infection with FMDV, even by experimental exposure. For
more information see - J Vet Med B 1996; 42(10): 595-9; Vet Arg 1996;
12(119): 620-7; and J Vet Med B 1999; 46: 157-61.
--
AA Schudel
Argentina
<incoalex@mail.retina.ar>
[The actual field experience involving camelids is most interesting.
However, that fact that camelids have been affected by FMD is certainly
documented in the literature as well as in field cases. We are grateful for
the answers provided, but unless there are other issues related to a spread
of this outbreak or the direct involvement of camelids, this thread is cut.
­ Mod.TG
